snippet.textDisplay:
The original was my everyday song and who better than Rahat ji to sing the classic?! I don't think anyone could do justice to it as he does. Is it just me or do their voices also match to some extent?
The only thing I really feel this version missed was the epic use of the matka (pot) in the original. I don't know what it is called as an instrument but it was heavily used in the original and they could've used that to maintain the soul. Nevertheless, my favourite comes to life again differently and I cannot be happier :)
